author: Chris Van Buskirk
title: Powerball climbs to estimated $760M ahead of Saturday drawing
text:
Feeling lucky?
The Powerball jackpot for the Saturday drawing rose to an estimated $760 million with a cash option prize of an estimated $382.5 million, lottery officials said Thursday. If someone wins the jackpot, it would be the sixth largest in Powerball history.
The Powerball was last hit on Oct. 11 and Saturday‚Äôs drawing will be the 34th since a $1.7 billion jackpot was won on a ticket sold in California, according to officials at the Massachusetts Lottery.
Two $50,000 prizes were won Wednesday on Quic Pic tickets sold at Fast Freddie‚Äôs in Beverly and Wellesley Variety in Wellesley.
To win the full estimated Powerball prize, all five white numbers must match plus the Powerball . The Wednesday Powerball drawing , which was not hit, was an estimated $685 million.
Powerball tickets are $2 each and can be played in 45 states, including Massachusetts, Washington, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands. Players can purchase tickets up until 9:50 p.m. Saturday at Massachusetts Lottery retailers.
Drawings are held every Monday, Wednesday, and Saturday at 10:59 p.m. in Tallahassee, Florida.
The winning $1.7 billion ticket earlier this year was sold at Midway Market & Liquor in Frazier Park.

author: HOLR MAGAZINE EDITORIAL
title: Katy Perry, Gayle King & Lauren S√°nchez Blast Off with Jeff Bezos
text:
Katy Perry, Gayle King, and Lauren S√°nchez to Join Space Mission with Jeff Bezos A New Milestone for Women in Space February 27, 2025: Katy Perry , journalist Gayle King , and media personality Lauren S√°nchez are set to be part of a groundbreaking space mission alongside Amazon founder Jeff Bezos . This flight marks a significant moment in space exploration and female representation in the field.
A Diverse Crew The mission will feature accomplished women from different industries, emphasizing the expanding role of women in science and technology. Perry, a global music icon and philanthropist, King, a respected journalist, and S√°nchez, a media entrepreneur and helicopter pilot, bring high-profile attention to this historic journey.
Breaking Barriers This mission aims to inspire future generations by proving that space travel is accessible to people beyond career astronauts. With Perry, King, and S√°nchez on board, the flight is expected to generate worldwide interest in women‚Äôs contributions to space exploration.
Mission Details While specific launch details and objectives are yet to be revealed, the mission is seen as a landmark event for gender equality in space travel. It also aligns with broader efforts to encourage more women to pursue careers in STEM fields.
A Vision for the Future Excitement is growing for this historic flight, which could pave the way for more diverse participation in space missions. As the world watches, this journey is set to inspire young women everywhere to dream big and reach for the stars.
Stay tuned for further updates on this remarkable mission.

text: [Franco Colapinto](https://www.eldestapeweb.com/tag/franco-colapinto) se prepara para su pr√≥xima pelea a mediados de septiembre luego de lo que fue su debut en la [F√≥rmula 1](https://www.eldestapeweb.com/tag/formula-1) de la mano de Williams. Por supuesto, el mismo sorprendi√≥ al pilarense que [culmin√≥ en el puesto n¬∞12 en Italia](https://www.eldestapeweb.com/deportes/formula-1/gran-debut-de-franco-colapinto-en-la-formula-1-termino-12-con-williams-20249111250). Si bien todav√≠a falta para el 2025, lo cierto es que desde el team Williams Racing ya tienen a sus dos pilotos confirmados pero no se olvidan de Colapinto y lo dejaron en claro. Quienes representar√°n a la escuder√≠a el a√±o pr√≥ximo ser√°n Alex Albon y Carlos Sainz Jr., por lo que todo indica que el argentino no tendr√° lugar. Sobre esto, Vowles asegur√≥: "Dependiendo de c√≥mo se desempe√±e, el futuro est√° en sus manos. Si lo hace bien permanecer√° aqu√≠ como piloto de reserva e invertiremos en √©l. As√≠ tambi√©n, no descart√≥ que exista la chance de que de seguir por el buen camino pase a otro equipo. Cabe destacar que el nacido en Pilar reemplaz√≥ a Logan Sargeant y se quedar√° el resto de la temporada. Cuando vuelve a correr Franco Colapinto en la F√≥rmula 1 La F√≥rmula 1 no da respiro y Franco Colapinto ya se prepara para su pr√≥ximo desaf√≠o. Despu√©s de un debut prometedor en el m√≠tico circuito de Monza, el piloto argentino se alista para enfrentar las calles de Bak√∫ en el Gran Premio de Azerbaiy√°n. Colapinto, que sorprendi√≥ a propios y extra√±os con su remontada en Italia, ahora tiene la oportunidad de demostrar su adaptabilidad en un trazado completamente diferente. La pr√≥xima cita de Franco Colapinto en la F√≥rmula 1 est√° a la vuelta de la esquina. El piloto argentino se prepara para enfrentar el Gran Premio de Azerbaiy√°n, que se llevar√° a cabo el 15 de septiembre en el circuito callejero de Bak√∫. author: Philip Kiew
title: Sarawak Keadilan youth supports royal‚Äôs decree to end ‚ÄòAllah‚Äô socks controversy
text:
Chiew said the state chapter rejects any irresponsible attitudes and actions by those who sow hatred using religion, without thinking of its greater consequences to the society.
MIRI (March 29): Angkatan Muda Keadilan (AMK) Sarawak supports the Yang di-Pertuan Agong Sultan Ibrahim ibni Sultan Iskandar‚Äôs decree for an end to KK Mart‚Äôs ‚ÄòAllah‚Äô socks controversy and let the law take its course.
AMK chief who is also Miri MP Chiew Choon Man said the state chapter rejects any irresponsible attitudes and actions by those who sow hatred using religion, without thinking of its greater consequences to the society.
‚ÄúWe condemn all kinds of actions that are disrespectful towards any religion and support the call by the King and Prime Minister Datuk Seri Anwar Ibrahim that any action that violates the law should be adjudicated through the national justice system.
‚ÄúThe tendency of many Malaysians acting as investigators and judges over what they perceive as offending issues will jeopardise peace and harmony in this country, thus we back the Prime Minister‚Äôs call for all decisions to be made according to the provisions of law.
Convenient store chain KK Mart was under intense scrutiny after several pairs of socks bearing the word ‚ÄòAllah‚Äô had been discovered at one of its outlets in Perak on March 13.
Umno Youth leader Dr Mohd Akmal Saleh had lodged a police report and subsequently rejected public apologies by the company and called for its boycott.

title: Christmas Eve weather: Severe thunderstorms forecast for parts of Australia - what the conditions look like in Sydney, Brisbane, Melbourne
text:
Severe thunderstorms forecast for Christmas EveNSW, Queensland and Victoria in firing line
NSW, Queensland and Victoria could face severe thunderstorms on Christmas Eve with residents told to prepare for the potential for hail, flash flooding and heavy rains.
Major storm concerns are held for ‚Äòthe vast majority of NSW‚Äô and Queensland, stretching all the way from Mackay to the state‚Äôs south east.
The Bureau of Meteorology‚Äôs senior meteorologist Angus Hines said the activity was forecast to peak on Sunday afternoon.
‚ÄòThe particular area where we‚Äôre likely to see severe thunderstorms is around Southeast Queensland including the Brisbane region and northeast NSW,‚Äô he said.
‚ÄòWe could see some of those thunderstorms get really big, really intense and they could potentially cause damaging to destructive wind gusts heavy to locally intense rainfall and large or even the giant sized hail as we saw yesterday.‚Äô
An outbreak of thunderstorms will affect many areas around NSW & Qld today -some of these thunderstorms may be severe. A low pressure system developing Christmas Eve near the Vic/NSW border will drag the storm risk sth across much of #Vic Xmas Day. Latest: https://t.co/4W35o8i7wJ pic.twitter.com/q9UioJ4xYh
‚Äî Bureau of Meteorology, Australia (@BOM_au) December 23, 2023
NSW, Queensland and Victoria could face severe thunderstorms on Christmas Eve with residents told to prepare for the potential for hail, flash flooding and heavy rains
On Sunday morning, BOM issued a severe thunderstorm warning for parts of central Queensland, with the potential for damaging wind, heavy rainfall and large hail.
This follows a spate of severe storms on Saturday, with high temperatures fuelling the weather activity.
The current warning is for areas across the southern Darling Downs, and Granite Belt district, however the weather authority said the activity will likely move eastwards in over the next few hours.
In NSW, showers and severe thunderstorms will mainly occur in the central and eastern inland areas, with lighter storms forecast near the coast and far west.
Up to 30mm of rain is forecast for Sydney on Sunday, with the chance for showers easing into the night.

Massive storms are forecast for Christmas Eve with the grim weather a departure from the characteristic, end-of-year heatwave
The Bureau warned a low pressure system developing on the NSW/ Victoria border will drag the storm risk ‚Äòacross much of Victoria‚Äô on Christmas Eve, bringing wet weather as the day progresses
Melbourne‚Äôs Carols by Candlelight also faces a potential washout, with a high chance of showers, and a possible thunderstorm forecast for the late afternoon and evening. The outdoors event will begin at the Sidney Myer Music Bowl from 8pm, with organisers adamant the show will go on rain, hail or shine.
The Bureau warned a low pressure system developing on the NSW/ Victoria border will drag the storm risk ‚Äòacross much of Victoria‚Äô on Christmas Eve, bringing wet weather as the day progresses.
‚ÄòShowers of course, by their nature, tend to be a little spotty a little hit and miss ‚Äì so there‚Äôs still a chance we‚Äôll get the carols in the dry but there‚Äôs a risk of showers across Melbourne City at that time of day,‚Äô said Mr Hines.While the eastern states could face a wet Christmas, multiple severe heatwave warnings remain in place for Western Australia.
The Bureau have issued a warning for the Pilbara, Gascoyne, North Interior and South Interior Districts, where temperatures could reach up to 45C.
The alert is currently in place until Boxing Day.
